2209
01:34:44,106 --> 01:34:46,346
Ni hao.

2210
01:34:46,346 --> 01:34:48,020
[Why is Sunny so surprised?]

2211
01:34:48,020 --> 01:34:49,514
Ni hao.

2212
01:34:49,514 --> 01:34:52,586
[Staff members suddenly pour out]
Ni hao. Ni hao.

2213
01:34:53,434 --> 01:34:54,680
[But...]

2214
01:34:54,680 --> 01:34:56,058
Wow, look at that...

2215
01:34:56,058 --> 01:34:58,936
[Endless stream of employees]
There are about 40 staff members.

2216
01:34:58,936 --> 01:35:03,466
[The vast hall is filled in an instant]

2217
01:35:03,466 --> 01:35:05,370
[The scale of the continent!]
That's incredible.

2218
01:35:05,370 --> 01:35:07,434
[It's on another level]

2219
01:35:08,090 --> 01:35:10,176
Sunny, come over here.

2220
01:35:12,666 --> 01:35:14,360
[Wow]

2221
01:35:14,360 --> 01:35:18,475
[All staff members lining up in two rows]

2222
01:35:18,475 --> 01:35:20,070
[The rookie finds her spot at the end]

2223
01:35:20,070 --> 01:35:22,648
[Scurrying]
Please stand in the women's line.

2224
01:35:24,634 --> 01:35:27,002
[Standing there without a clue]

2225
01:35:27,002 --> 01:35:29,722
That must be so nerve-racking.

2226
01:35:29,722 --> 01:35:32,387
[The owner stands before the staff]
- Good morning. - Good morning.

2227
01:35:32,387 --> 01:35:34,266
[Calling out names one by one]

2228
01:35:34,266 --> 01:35:36,890
That's right. They do roll call like this.

2229
01:35:36,890 --> 01:35:39,759
[Morning assembly starts with roll call]
They call out the names...

2230
01:35:40,490 --> 01:35:42,314
[A morning in China, different from Italy]

2231
01:35:42,314 --> 01:35:44,522
- It's like a school.
- What?

2232
01:35:44,522 --> 01:35:46,410
It's just like a school.

2233
01:35:46,410 --> 01:35:48,362
- Lim.
- Here.

2234
01:35:48,362 --> 01:35:49,992
Sunny!

2235
01:35:50,696 --> 01:35:52,906
- Huh?
- Yes!

2236
01:35:52,906 --> 01:35:56,090
[Oh, right... My name is Sunny]
- Why? - You shouldn't forget your name.

2237
01:35:56,090 --> 01:35:58,500
I wasn't used to the name Sunny yet.

2238
01:35:58,500 --> 01:36:00,090
During the roll call earlier,

2239
01:36:00,090 --> 01:36:01,642
I answered after a long pause.

2240
01:36:01,642 --> 01:36:03,882
I'm not used to being called Sunny.

2241
01:36:03,882 --> 01:36:05,962
[Snap out of it]
It didn't register at first.

2242
01:36:05,962 --> 01:36:09,770
Our new youngest member from Korea...

2243
01:36:09,770 --> 01:36:11,290
I'd like to introduce her.

2244
01:36:11,290 --> 01:36:13,578
[The buzz about the Korean boxer]
Her name is Sunny.

2245
01:36:14,442 --> 01:36:15,754
[Glance]

2246
01:36:15,754 --> 01:36:17,050
[Glance]

2247
01:36:17,050 --> 01:36:20,602
Sunny, come out and say a few words.

2248
01:36:20,602 --> 01:36:22,890
[Go to the front?]

2249
01:36:22,890 --> 01:36:24,970
[All eyes on her!]
[I'm getting nervous too]

2250
01:36:24,970 --> 01:36:26,180
She must be so nervous.

2251
01:36:26,180 --> 01:36:27,274
Hello.

2252
01:36:27,274 --> 01:36:30,762
I'm Sunny from Korea.

2253
01:36:30,762 --> 01:36:32,602
I look forward to working with you.

2254
01:36:32,602 --> 01:36:34,314
[Mission safe without exposure]
Thank you.

2255
01:36:34,314 --> 01:36:36,040
That's a relief, though.

2256
01:36:36,040 --> 01:36:37,594
They really thought I was a boxer.

2257
01:36:37,594 --> 01:36:39,690
[The resume worked perfectly]
If even one person recognizes her...

2258
01:36:39,690 --> 01:36:41,188
- Right, right.
- If that happens...

2259
01:36:41,188 --> 01:36:42,794
- No one suspected a thing.
- Seriously.

2260
01:36:42,794 --> 01:36:45,482
- Recite the slogan!
- Be people of character.

2261
01:36:45,482 --> 01:36:47,050
Do your work properly.

2262
01:36:47,050 --> 01:36:50,310
[Memorizing]
Service and customers come first.

2263
01:36:50,310 --> 01:36:51,882
[Morning assembly ends with the slogan]

2264
01:36:51,882 --> 01:36:54,132
[Wow, this is great]
This is really good.

2265
01:36:54,132 --> 01:36:55,818
[Deeply inspired]
I should try this later.

2266
01:36:55,818 --> 01:36:57,114
You're going to do that?

2267
01:36:57,114 --> 01:36:59,466
[Sam Kitchen morning assembly]
Suddenly bringing in things he learned...

2268
01:36:59,466 --> 01:37:01,194
Lining everyone up all of a sudden.

2269
01:37:01,194 --> 01:37:02,907
[Heading to stations for work]
Like when a department store opens.

2270
01:37:02,907 --> 01:37:04,954
- Like in the old days.
- I think it's a good idea.

2271
01:37:04,954 --> 01:37:08,705
[The chef brigade]
[Sunny follows them into the kitchen]

2272
01:37:08,705 --> 01:37:11,141
[Finally enters the kitchen]
I'm excited to see this kitchen.

2273
01:37:11,141 --> 01:37:12,827
- It must be huge.
- I'm so curious too.

2274
01:37:12,827 --> 01:37:14,042
[Can't even imagine the scale]

2275
01:37:14,042 --> 01:37:15,850
A kitchen that handles 500 seats...

2276
01:37:15,850 --> 01:37:17,178
How big could it be?

2277
01:37:17,178 --> 01:37:20,122
[Focused]
I bet it's massive.

2278
01:37:20,122 --> 01:37:21,962
[Finally entering the kitchen...]

2279
01:37:21,962 --> 01:37:24,410
[Eyes wide open]

2280
01:37:30,862 --> 01:37:33,438
[The massive banquet kitchen?]
- The kitchen... - What's it like?

2281
01:37:34,910 --> 01:37:38,181
[Starting with the massive open kitchen
for dumplings and cold appetizers]

2282
01:37:39,054 --> 01:37:41,758
[Row 1: Plating]

2283
01:37:41,758 --> 01:37:44,280
[Row 2: Prep]
[Row 3: Cooking]

2284
01:37:45,270 --> 01:37:47,278
This is incredible!

2285
01:37:47,278 --> 01:37:49,134
I might get lost in here.

2286
01:37:49,134 --> 01:37:50,350
It's so big.

2287
01:37:50,350 --> 01:37:53,246
[Rows 1, 2, 3, and 4: Kitchen]

2288
01:37:53,246 --> 01:37:54,863
- It's massive.
- The scale is...

2289
01:37:54,863 --> 01:37:57,406
[Like a military kitchen]
- It's on another level. - Yes.

2290
01:37:57,406 --> 01:37:59,800
[7 woks cooking simultaneously]

2291
01:38:00,558 --> 01:38:03,358
[7 people just for prep]

2292
01:38:04,126 --> 01:38:08,437
[A massive kitchen where 40 staff
serve 500 people]

2293
01:38:09,566 --> 01:38:12,094
[Sunny's first mission?]
First, try slicing some chili peppers.

2294
01:38:12,094 --> 01:38:14,810
And some meat too.

2295
01:38:14,810 --> 01:38:17,590
We'll start with a knife skills test.

2296
01:38:17,590 --> 01:38:19,198
A knife skills test? How nerve-wracking.

2297
01:38:19,198 --> 01:38:20,510
- A knife skills test?
- Yes.

2298
01:38:20,510 --> 01:38:22,590
- A knife skills test?
- Right from the start.

2299
01:38:22,590 --> 01:38:25,836
[Identity at risk]
Her cover will be blown.

2300
01:38:25,836 --> 01:38:28,198
- Shouldn't she pretend to be bad?
- True.

2301
01:38:28,198 --> 01:38:29,758
But how can she pretend to be bad?

2302
01:38:29,758 --> 01:38:31,960
[Can she hide 24 years of experience?]
Her muscle memory will take over.

2303
01:38:31,960 --> 01:38:33,750
We always test newcomers first.

2304
01:38:33,750 --> 01:38:38,718
We have them slice things like meat or chili.

2305
01:38:38,718 --> 01:38:41,182
We assign roles based on their knife skills.

2306
01:38:42,094 --> 01:38:45,630
[Controlling her deeply ingrained skills
is the key]

2307
01:38:45,630 --> 01:38:47,582
Let me introduce our youngest, Xu Jian Kai.

2308
01:38:47,582 --> 01:38:49,326
[Bows quickly]
He'll be your partner today.

2309
01:38:49,326 --> 01:38:50,830
You can call him Xiao Xu.

2310
01:38:50,830 --> 01:38:52,680
- He must be the youngest.
- He's so MZ.

2311
01:38:52,680 --> 01:38:55,742
- He looks really young.
- You're right. He's definitely Gen MZ.

2312
01:38:55,742 --> 01:38:57,500
[A certified MZ member]
Exactly MZ.

2313
01:38:57,500 --> 01:39:00,766
[Prep No. 3, 4 years exp. Xu Jian Kai]
- 'MZ' sounds like an insult. - He's MZ.

2314
01:39:00,766 --> 01:39:03,070
[Prep No. 2, 15 years exp. Liu Dai Yu]

2315
01:39:03,070 --> 01:39:04,878
[Prep No. 1, 23 years exp. Tang Wei]

2316
01:39:04,878 --> 01:39:05,998
Prep?

2317
01:39:05,998 --> 01:39:07,358
[Hierarchy: Prep Head]
Yes, Prep.

2318
01:39:07,358 --> 01:39:09,050
- So this section is called Prep.
- Yes.

2319
01:39:09,050 --> 01:39:10,894
Prep, Wok, Noodle.

2320
01:39:10,894 --> 01:39:13,529
[Stages Sunny must go through]
It's all divided like this.

2321
01:39:14,174 --> 01:39:16,606
You can think of the general kitchen duties,

2322
01:39:16,606 --> 01:39:18,624
[Step 1: Prep]
as all start at the Prep station.

2323
01:39:18,624 --> 01:39:21,427
Orders are handled at the Prep station.

2324
01:39:21,427 --> 01:39:24,542
They also manage the ingredients there.

2325
01:39:24,542 --> 01:39:27,806
To put out a single dish,
they prep and separate everything like this.

2326
01:39:27,806 --> 01:39:29,374
There's a separate team for cooking,

2327
01:39:29,374 --> 01:39:31,200
[Next step: Wok]
- and a team for prep. - Yes.

2328
01:39:31,200 --> 01:39:34,360
The terms are so different from Italy.

2329
01:39:34,360 --> 01:39:36,859
The ones at the Wok station
are the most senior.

2330
01:39:36,859 --> 01:39:39,180
- The most senior.
- The youngest starts at Prep.

2331
01:39:39,180 --> 01:39:43,524
[Sunny's goal: reach Wok in 5 days]
So you started at the Prep station.

2332
01:39:44,197 --> 01:39:45,850
[Knife test to determine work placement]

2333
01:39:45,850 --> 01:39:47,150
That must be nerve-wracking.

2334
01:39:47,150 --> 01:39:50,958
[Evaluators: The Boss & Prep Chief]
- Let's start this afternoon. - Good.

2335
01:39:50,958 --> 01:39:52,910
[No. 1 Prep Chief's demonstration]
I'll show you.

2336
01:39:52,910 --> 01:39:54,286
Show her. Show her.

2337
01:39:54,286 --> 01:39:56,078
First, slice this...

2338
01:39:56,078 --> 01:39:57,566
[Test Item 1: Chunking]

2339
01:39:57,566 --> 01:39:58,923
[Test Item 2: Diagonal slicing]

2340
01:39:58,923 --> 01:40:02,638
[Test Item 3: Shredding]
Try these three techniques.

2341
01:40:02,638 --> 01:40:04,878
[Input complete]
Understood.

2342
01:40:04,878 --> 01:40:06,514
[The knife test begins]
- Give it a try. - Okay.

2343
01:40:06,514 --> 01:40:09,950
[Instinctive skill]
She gripped it like a pro when she flipped it.

2344
01:40:09,950 --> 01:40:11,886
- Exactly.
- This knife is really heavy.

2345
01:40:11,886 --> 01:40:12,958
Is it heavy?

2346
01:40:12,958 --> 01:40:14,622
[Luckily, they didn't notice]

2347
01:40:15,260 --> 01:40:16,710
[The first cut]
Wait a second.

2348
01:40:16,710 --> 01:40:19,554
- Is this right?
- Yes, that's right.

2349
01:40:20,158 --> 01:40:22,126
She shouldn't be too good at it.

2350
01:40:22,126 --> 01:40:24,309
[The key is controlling her skill level]

2351
01:40:24,309 --> 01:40:26,142
[Checking again]
- Is this okay? - Good, good.

2352
01:40:26,142 --> 01:40:27,374
I kept asking them questions.

2353
01:40:27,374 --> 01:40:29,502
[After every single cut]
"Is this okay?"

2354
01:40:29,502 --> 01:40:32,284
[Constant confirmation]
- Is this okay? - Good, good.

2355
01:40:32,284 --> 01:40:34,286
[He responds to just a glance]
That's right. Good.

2356
01:40:34,286 --> 01:40:35,742
- Is it okay?
- It's not bad.

2357
01:40:35,742 --> 01:40:39,094
If I just start chopping away like a pro,

2358
01:40:39,094 --> 01:40:40,682
I'm afraid they'll say, "Who is she?"

2359
01:40:40,682 --> 01:40:42,144
So I'm cutting slowly on purpose.

2360
01:40:42,144 --> 01:40:43,998
[Don't be greedy on day one]
I can't show off.

2361
01:40:43,998 --> 01:40:45,422
Exactly.

2362
01:40:45,422 --> 01:40:48,110
[She's sticking to her rookie persona]

2363
01:40:48,110 --> 01:40:50,014
[The owner is suddenly watching]

2364
01:40:51,310 --> 01:40:52,357
[Gulp]

2365
01:40:52,357 --> 01:40:55,876
[Pressure]
The owner came over and kept watching me.

2366
01:40:55,876 --> 01:40:59,854
[Surveillance is universal for all bosses...]
Bosses are always doing things like this.

2367
01:40:59,854 --> 01:41:02,830
[Then!]
- The grandmother... - Even the grandmother?

2368
01:41:02,830 --> 01:41:07,070
[Even the final boss, Grandma, watches Sunny]

2369
01:41:07,814 --> 01:41:09,854
[Six eyes watching Sunny]
There are so many people,

2370
01:41:09,854 --> 01:41:11,790
so many of them are staring at me.

2371
01:41:11,790 --> 01:41:15,662
[With so many employees,
the number of eyes is doubled]

2372
01:41:15,662 --> 01:41:18,094
[Working hard despite the laser-like gaze]

2373
01:41:19,054 --> 01:41:21,255
[Slowly]
This is just...

2374
01:41:21,255 --> 01:41:24,958
[Chili cut too perfectly for a beginner]
The spacing is too even.

2375
01:41:24,958 --> 01:41:26,510
[Thumbs up!]
- Okay. - Okay?

2376
01:41:26,510 --> 01:41:28,078
Good.

2377
01:41:28,078 --> 01:41:30,622
[She's good at chopping!]

2378
01:41:30,622 --> 01:41:32,810
- You can't fool them like this.
- Slow down.

2379
01:41:32,810 --> 01:41:35,990
[Is the knife test over?]
- He said you did well. - Right.

2380
01:41:35,990 --> 01:41:37,160
[Test number two]

2381
01:41:37,160 --> 01:41:38,620
- Gungchae.
- Gungchae.

2382
01:41:38,620 --> 01:41:40,094
It's gungchae. Gungchae.

2383
01:41:40,094 --> 01:41:42,950
- It's eaten a lot in China.
- That's right.

2384
01:41:42,950 --> 01:41:46,014
[Shredding gungchae stems]

2385
01:41:46,014 --> 01:41:48,622
There's something to keep in mind
when shredding the stems.

2386
01:41:48,622 --> 01:41:51,294
You have to cut it to a consistent thickness.

2387
01:41:51,294 --> 01:41:53,726
You need to pay attention to this part.

2388
01:41:53,726 --> 01:41:57,358
[Demonstration by the Head of Knife Station]

2389
01:41:57,358 --> 01:41:59,854
[First, slice them at regular intervals]

2390
01:42:01,198 --> 01:42:03,918
[Then shred them to the same thickness]

2391
01:42:03,918 --> 01:42:05,294
[Ta-da]

2392
01:42:05,294 --> 01:42:07,880
He's so good at it.

2393
01:42:07,880 --> 01:42:10,494
[Sunny's turn]
Try cutting it like this.

2394
01:42:11,134 --> 01:42:13,694
Pay attention to the thickness.

2395
01:42:13,694 --> 01:42:16,557
She's deliberately controlling her speed.

2396
01:42:16,557 --> 01:42:18,950
[Eyes fixed on Sunny's knife skills]
She must be so nervous.

2397
01:42:18,950 --> 01:42:21,614
I didn't realize they were
staring that closely.

2398
01:42:21,614 --> 01:42:22,840
Let me see.

2399
01:42:22,840 --> 01:42:25,800
This is a bit thick.

2400
01:42:27,210 --> 01:42:29,070
[Head's vs. Sunny's]

2401
01:42:29,070 --> 01:42:32,214
- The thickness is different.
- You're right.

2402
01:42:32,214 --> 01:42:35,342
[24-year veteran criticized for her cutting]
You'll waste ingredients this way.

2403
01:42:35,342 --> 01:42:37,518
[Lips sealed]

2404
01:42:38,590 --> 01:42:39,678
Lips sealed.

2405
01:42:39,678 --> 01:42:41,358
[Is it nerves? Or a smoke screen?]

2406
01:42:42,158 --> 01:42:47,502
[She continues cutting
despite the constant criticism]

2407
01:42:47,502 --> 01:42:50,750
[Hmm...]

2408
01:42:50,750 --> 01:42:53,486
Don't slice it slowly.
You have to chop it down in one go.

2409
01:42:53,486 --> 01:42:56,478
[A stern command]
You have to chop it down in one go.

2410
01:42:56,478 --> 01:42:58,708
In one go.

2411
01:42:58,708 --> 01:43:00,614
- In Chinese cooking, you chop it down.
- Yes.

2412
01:43:00,614 --> 01:43:03,182
- You're pushing the knife instead of slicing.
- That's right.

2413
01:43:03,182 --> 01:43:05,274
- Like western style.
- It is western style.

2414
01:43:05,870 --> 01:43:08,463
[Grandma is not at all
impressed with Sunny's cutting]

2415
01:43:09,999 --> 01:43:11,726
[Even taking the knife away]
I'll show you.

2416
01:43:11,726 --> 01:43:13,326
Come here and watch closely.

2417
01:43:13,326 --> 01:43:15,102
Stand on this side and watch.

2418
01:43:15,102 --> 01:43:17,678
Leave that for now.

2419
01:43:18,862 --> 01:43:22,014
I just have to make them think,
"She's a total beginner."

2420
01:43:22,014 --> 01:43:24,578
I have to give them that impression.

2421
01:43:25,252 --> 01:43:28,270
[Staying true to her undercover role]
I bet she wants to cut so much faster.

2422
01:43:28,270 --> 01:43:30,101
But she can't.

2423
01:43:30,101 --> 01:43:31,342
[Cutting as slowly as possible]

2424
01:43:31,342 --> 01:43:33,822
- But she's acting too much like a rookie.
- It's really slow.

2425
01:43:33,822 --> 01:43:36,510
She really acted like a total beginner.

2426
01:43:36,510 --> 01:43:37,806
Slowly, slowly... almost like...

2427
01:43:37,806 --> 01:43:40,462
- They check the thickness of every piece.
- This is a bit thick.

2428
01:43:40,462 --> 01:43:42,574
- This thickness won't do.
- But honestly...

2429
01:43:42,574 --> 01:43:45,550
[Regarding Sunny's poor cutting skills]
They're teaching her everything.

2430
01:43:45,550 --> 01:43:48,894
[Wiping her face in frustration]

2431
01:43:48,894 --> 01:43:52,126
- You're cutting it too thick.
- You're right.

2432
01:43:52,894 --> 01:43:55,166
[What will be the result of the cutting test?]

2433
01:43:55,166 --> 01:43:56,462
- Sunny.
- Yes?

2434
01:43:56,462 --> 01:43:59,950
I've observed your cutting skills.

2435
01:43:59,950 --> 01:44:04,638
The technique is okay, but the speed is
too slow. And you're wasting ingredients.

2436
01:44:04,638 --> 01:44:07,022
So we think...

2437
01:44:07,022 --> 01:44:09,753
Start with chopping green chilies.

2438
01:44:09,753 --> 01:44:11,278
[Demoted back to level one]
She failed.

2439
01:44:11,278 --> 01:44:13,335
Go to the green chilies.

2440
01:44:14,220 --> 01:44:15,774
Chop this whole container of green chilies.

2441
01:44:15,774 --> 01:44:18,878
When you're done, bring more
from outside and keep chopping.

2442
01:44:18,878 --> 01:44:20,222
I understand.

2443
01:44:20,222 --> 01:44:22,484
She's down to the green chili level now.

2444
01:44:22,484 --> 01:44:24,526
- Level one, level one.
- Yes, level one.

2445
01:44:24,526 --> 01:44:26,942
[Chopping chilies for 500 servings.
Work begins in earnest]

2446
01:44:28,601 --> 01:44:30,920
[The other cooks seem curious
about the new rookie, Sunny]

2447
01:44:30,920 --> 01:44:33,870
Sneaking over...

2448
01:44:33,870 --> 01:44:37,502
This... this is your dishcloth, Sunny.

2449
01:44:37,502 --> 01:44:39,370
Use it to wipe your knife later.

2450
01:44:39,370 --> 01:44:42,590
Okay, thank you.

2451
01:44:42,590 --> 01:44:45,278
[The former rookie looks after the new rookie]

2452
01:44:47,342 --> 01:44:49,582
[Sneaking a peek]

2453
01:44:50,430 --> 01:44:54,142
[Checks her surroundings and
preps a handful of chilies]

2454
01:44:55,182 --> 01:44:58,462
[Hyper-focused]

2455
01:45:00,140 --> 01:45:03,022
[Chopping the chilies rapidly
while the boss isn't looking]

2456
01:45:03,022 --> 01:45:06,174
[Incomparable to Sam Kwon's potatoes]
It's nothing like the potatoes earlier.

2457
01:45:06,174 --> 01:45:09,022
Right, she has to prep for 500 people here.

2458
01:45:09,022 --> 01:45:10,686
My eyes keep tearing up.

2459
01:45:10,686 --> 01:45:12,827
[The boss appears]

2460
01:45:16,430 --> 01:45:20,158
[Goes back to slow chopping]

2461
01:45:21,150 --> 01:45:24,670
[The boss watches Sunny chop from behind]
- Is the boss still there? - Yes, he is.

2462
01:45:24,670 --> 01:45:26,270
When she was chopping chilies,

2463
01:45:26,270 --> 01:45:29,070
I thought her basics were solid.

2464
01:45:29,070 --> 01:45:30,974
A Chinese cleaver is quite heavy,

2465
01:45:30,974 --> 01:45:35,134
but she seemed to have mastered

2466
01:45:35,134 --> 01:45:37,492
the knife skills very quickly.

2467
01:45:37,492 --> 01:45:40,634
[The boss notices Sunny's hidden talent]
She seemed to pick it up very quickly.

2468
01:45:40,634 --> 01:45:44,942
Even with unfamiliar tasks,
I think she'll adapt fast.

2469
01:45:44,942 --> 01:45:47,758
[Chilies chopped in no time]
We have to make a good impression.

2470
01:45:47,758 --> 01:45:50,478
[Finished the last of the chilies]

2471
01:45:51,710 --> 01:45:54,990
[Reporting to the Section Head!]
- I'm done chopping. - Okay.

2472
01:45:55,678 --> 01:45:58,238
[What is that?]

2473
01:45:59,134 --> 01:46:01,022
[A mysterious creature?]

2474
01:46:01,710 --> 01:46:04,286
[Glance]

2475
01:46:06,672 --> 01:46:08,376
What is this?

2476
01:46:09,180 --> 01:46:10,254
This is a swamp eel.

2477
01:46:10,254 --> 01:46:12,270
- Swamp eel?
- Swamp eel.

2478
01:46:12,270 --> 01:46:13,406
Swamp eel.

2479
01:46:13,406 --> 01:46:16,046
It's called "Shanyu."

2480
01:46:16,046 --> 01:46:19,552
[Shanyu: A long, thin fish]
I didn't know people ate this.

2481
01:46:19,552 --> 01:46:21,038
I've only seen it in biology books.

2482
01:46:21,038 --> 01:46:23,411
- Really?
- From what I've heard...

2483
01:46:24,540 --> 01:46:27,102
[Mainly used in soups or stir-fries]

2484
01:46:28,310 --> 01:46:31,790
[It's even served over rice!]

2485
01:46:32,478 --> 01:46:35,406
[Unfamiliar, but prized for its tender texture]

2486
01:46:36,142 --> 01:46:38,279
It looks really delicious.

2487
01:46:40,032 --> 01:46:43,337
[Familiar ingredient to the Chinese]
So they eat this.

2488
01:46:44,430 --> 01:46:46,999
[A chance for a promotion to prep fish!]
- Give it a try. - Okay.

2489
01:46:48,910 --> 01:46:51,132
Don't be afraid.

2490
01:46:51,870 --> 01:46:53,150
[Squish]

2491
01:46:53,150 --> 01:46:55,102
[Lips pursed tight]
Don't be afraid.

2492
01:46:55,102 --> 01:46:58,174
[The warrior's unexpected side?]
Don't you usually grab ingredients firmly?

2493
01:46:58,174 --> 01:47:00,862
Yes, but it's just so unfamiliar to me.

2494
01:47:00,862 --> 01:47:02,419
Since it's an unfamiliar ingredient.

2495
01:47:02,419 --> 01:47:04,646
[Swamp eel is rare in Korea]
But it's not common in Korea.

2496
01:47:04,646 --> 01:47:06,670
- It's almost impossible to find.
- That's right.

2497
01:47:06,670 --> 01:47:09,344
This is a bit scary, isn't it?

2498
01:47:10,318 --> 01:47:12,494
[Unfamiliar slippery texture]

2499
01:47:12,494 --> 01:47:16,351
You have to cut off the head.

2500
01:47:17,200 --> 01:47:19,640
Do it like this, and...

2501
01:47:22,894 --> 01:47:24,302
Look at how the knife sticks.

2502
01:47:24,302 --> 01:47:25,758
The knife is heavy.

2503
01:47:25,758 --> 01:47:27,100
It's sticking to the board.

2504
01:47:27,100 --> 01:47:28,558
It's just getting stuck in the wood.

2505
01:47:28,558 --> 01:47:30,574
- Is that a cleaver or an axe?
- You have to cut the head off too.

2506
01:47:30,574 --> 01:47:32,254
[Still not cut through]

2507
01:47:32,990 --> 01:47:34,894
[Watching closely]

2508
01:47:34,894 --> 01:47:37,038
The owner is quite sharp.

2509
01:47:37,038 --> 01:47:39,973
[Creeping up]
He's watching with a hawk's eye.

2510
01:47:40,702 --> 01:47:44,222
[Peeking]
- Like this? - You can discard this.

2511
01:47:44,222 --> 01:47:46,846
[Chopping raw ingredients]
[They're curious about Sunny's skills]

2512
01:47:46,846 --> 01:47:48,700
Like this?

2513
01:47:48,700 --> 01:47:50,858
[Glance]
You can discard this.

2514
01:47:52,486 --> 01:47:54,646
It's not cutting well.

2515
01:47:56,323 --> 01:47:58,694
It's not cut through here either.

2516
01:48:01,655 --> 01:48:04,039
[Trying to fix the uncut swamp eel...]
It didn't cut through.

2517
01:48:04,766 --> 01:48:05,870
The owner is... wow.

2518
01:48:05,870 --> 01:48:10,030
[The owner again]

2519
01:48:10,830 --> 01:48:13,086
[Glance]

2520
01:48:13,806 --> 01:48:15,854
[Feeling the pressure]
Since this is actually...

2521
01:48:15,854 --> 01:48:17,134
something that will be served...

2522
01:48:17,134 --> 01:48:18,310
- to the customers.
- Yes.

2523
01:48:18,310 --> 01:48:19,664
He has to be sensitive about it.

2524
01:48:19,664 --> 01:48:21,678
- It's for the customers.
- It's for the customers.

2525
01:48:21,678 --> 01:48:23,100
Throw this away.

2526
01:48:23,100 --> 01:48:26,958
[Feeling her intense gaze from behind]

2527
01:48:28,142 --> 01:48:29,480
[Okay, I can't hold back anymore]

2528
01:48:29,480 --> 01:48:30,638
Okay, okay.

2529
01:48:30,638 --> 01:48:32,140
Okay.

2530
01:48:32,830 --> 01:48:34,814
[Getting into the zone!]

2531
01:48:35,399 --> 01:48:37,006
[Starts swinging the cleaver with power]

2532
01:48:37,006 --> 01:48:39,790
Is that how I should cut it?

2533
01:48:39,790 --> 01:48:40,910
Chop, chop, chop.

2534
01:48:40,910 --> 01:48:44,380
[One-shot, one-kill chopping]

2535
01:48:44,380 --> 01:48:47,774
[Starts chopping using power and snap]

2536
01:48:48,650 --> 01:48:51,118
[Glance]

2537
01:48:51,770 --> 01:48:54,126
[Seeing she's doing well,
the owner finally leaves]

2538
01:48:55,038 --> 01:48:58,606
[Focusing!]

2539
01:48:59,310 --> 01:49:02,186
[Sunny chops vigorously with speed]

2540
01:49:02,186 --> 01:49:03,654
You can do it like this.

2541
01:49:03,654 --> 01:49:05,310
Okay, last one.

2542
01:49:05,310 --> 01:49:09,710
[The full container is now empty!]

2543
01:49:10,790 --> 01:49:13,758
[Startled She said she was a boxer...]

2544
01:49:14,446 --> 01:49:18,270
[Cleaning the board immediately]

2545
01:49:19,214 --> 01:49:22,650
[Overcoming the crisis with
24 years of experience]

2546
01:49:23,374 --> 01:49:27,246
She seems to be adapting well, right?

2547
01:49:27,246 --> 01:49:29,150
Should I have her chop the frogs too?

2548
01:49:29,150 --> 01:49:30,734
I think she can handle the frogs.

2549
01:49:30,734 --> 01:49:32,670
Frogs?

2550
01:49:32,670 --> 01:49:35,431
[The prep chef prepares the next level]
They use frogs too.

2551
01:49:37,102 --> 01:49:39,166
[Wait, is that...]

2552
01:49:39,166 --> 01:49:40,846
Look at her face.

2553
01:49:40,846 --> 01:49:44,158
I think she wants to close her eyes.
Aren't her eyes basically closed right now?

2554
01:49:44,158 --> 01:49:46,807
Do you want to learn how to do this?

2555
01:49:48,878 --> 01:49:52,078
[Snapping back to reality]

2556
01:49:52,078 --> 01:49:55,774
[One hurdle after another]
[First swamp eels, now frogs...]

2557
01:49:55,774 --> 01:49:57,486
[I am Sunny]
<i>I'm Sunny, after all.</i>

2558
01:49:57,486 --> 01:50:00,282
<i>I'll get it done no matter what.</i>

2559
01:50:01,566 --> 01:50:02,950
[Frogs weren't in my plans...]

2560
01:50:02,950 --> 01:50:06,078
- In Korea, it's a very unfamiliar ingredient.
- Yes.

2561
01:50:06,078 --> 01:50:07,454
Give it a try.

2562
01:50:07,454 --> 01:50:08,890
O... Okay. Sure.

2563
01:50:08,890 --> 01:50:11,630
- Can you do it?
- Okay, okay.

2564
01:50:11,630 --> 01:50:14,750
[Spirit awakened: I am Sunny]
<i>I'll do it no matter what.</i>

2565
01:50:14,750 --> 01:50:18,172
[Stepping up for now...]
- Can you do it? - Okay, okay.

2566
01:50:20,798 --> 01:50:22,302
[Flinch]
It's moving! It's moving!

2567
01:50:22,302 --> 01:50:24,766
It's moving.

2568
01:50:24,766 --> 01:50:27,761
[Making a fuss]
- It's moving! - It's moving.

2569
01:50:28,590 --> 01:50:32,014
[Confidence shattered by the visual]

2570
01:50:32,014 --> 01:50:34,286
Are you scared of this?

2571
01:50:34,286 --> 01:50:36,206
This is nothing.

2572
01:50:36,206 --> 01:50:39,150
- It's moving.
- Seeing it move, she looks a bit scared.

2573
01:50:39,150 --> 01:50:40,862
[Grandma, comes to see the commotion]

2574
01:50:40,862 --> 01:50:43,709
Can you handle this?

2575
01:50:43,709 --> 01:50:45,598
[Communication error]
I haven't tried eating it.

2576
01:50:45,598 --> 01:50:47,614
- This is a bullfrog.
- A bullfrog.

2577
01:50:47,614 --> 01:50:49,523
I know bullfrogs.

2578
01:50:50,247 --> 01:50:53,324
[A Chinese health food]
Frogs are considered a health food.

2579
01:50:53,324 --> 01:50:54,494
It's a health food.

2580
01:50:54,494 --> 01:50:56,846
[Flash-fried to remove the gamey smell]

2581
01:50:56,846 --> 01:50:58,206
It's like chicken.

2582
01:50:58,206 --> 01:51:02,127
[Coated in spicy mala for a numbing kick]
- It tastes like chicken. - It's very similar.

2583
01:51:02,127 --> 01:51:06,309
[The chewy texture of chicken tenderloin!]
If it's fried well, you eat the bones too.

2584
01:51:06,309 --> 01:51:08,062
It's a very popular dish.

2585
01:51:08,062 --> 01:51:09,582
It's selling really well.

2586
01:51:09,582 --> 01:51:12,062
- This looks delicious.
- Can you do it?

2587
01:51:12,062 --> 01:51:13,934
Do you want to try?

2588
01:51:13,934 --> 01:51:15,934
Don't do it if you're scared.

2589
01:51:15,934 --> 01:51:17,230
[I am Sunny]
Let me try.

2590
01:51:17,230 --> 01:51:18,478
Take it slow.

2591
01:51:18,478 --> 01:51:20,046
Don't be afraid.

2592
01:51:20,046 --> 01:51:22,030
[Tossed aside]

2593
01:51:22,030 --> 01:51:24,590
[Laughter]

2594
01:51:24,590 --> 01:51:26,014
- Give it a try.
- Okay.

2595
01:51:26,014 --> 01:51:27,822
You can be rough with it.

2596
01:51:27,822 --> 01:51:29,326
Do I cut it like this? Like this?

2597
01:51:29,326 --> 01:51:31,893
Hold it here. Right here.

2598
01:51:32,622 --> 01:51:34,830
Like this? Like this?

2599
01:51:34,830 --> 01:51:36,606
[She plucks up the courage to strike...]

2600
01:51:36,606 --> 01:51:38,286
[Twitch]

2601
01:51:38,286 --> 01:51:39,566
It's moving! What do I do?

2602
01:51:39,566 --> 01:51:43,467
[200% immersion]

2603
01:51:43,467 --> 01:51:46,060
- Could you do it?
- I don't think I can.

2604
01:51:46,060 --> 01:51:49,710
[Whoa... Whoa, whoa!]

2605
01:51:50,557 --> 01:51:55,637
[The Grandma finds the "boxer's" fear adorable]
She's afraid of frogs.

2606
01:51:56,382 --> 01:51:58,606
It can be scary.

2607
01:51:59,454 --> 01:52:03,843
[Sunny's reaction lightens the mood]
- She seems scared. - It can be scary.

2608
01:52:03,843 --> 01:52:05,742
[Protecting the youngest]
Don't make her do it.

2609
01:52:05,742 --> 01:52:07,450
Just once! I'll try one more time.

2610
01:52:07,450 --> 01:52:09,500
[Panicked, she starts speaking Korean]
What do I do?

2611
01:52:09,500 --> 01:52:12,398
- It's just the muscles contracting.
- Oh, my goodness.

2612
01:52:12,398 --> 01:52:14,334
Muscles? Okay.

2613
01:52:14,334 --> 01:52:17,939
What do I do? What do I do?

2614
01:52:19,640 --> 01:52:21,130
Okay, okay.

2615
01:52:21,130 --> 01:52:23,006
Okay, okay.

2616
01:52:23,006 --> 01:52:25,422
This isn't easy.

2617
01:52:25,422 --> 01:52:26,790
Oh, dear.

2618
01:52:26,790 --> 01:52:32,702
[Forgetting her undercover role for a bit]
Sunny is scared of frogs.

2619
01:52:33,301 --> 01:52:35,950
- Cut it and then...
- Flip it over.

2620
01:52:36,638 --> 01:52:38,846
[Twitch]

2621
01:52:38,846 --> 01:52:42,142
[Backing away slowly]

2622
01:52:42,142 --> 01:52:44,654
Make the pieces a bit bigger.

2623
01:52:44,654 --> 01:52:46,526
- Bigger?
- Yes, bigger.

2624
01:52:46,526 --> 01:52:48,775
Don't cut them so small. Make them bigger.

2625
01:52:48,775 --> 01:52:51,278
- Is this okay?
- I'll show you.

2626
01:52:51,278 --> 01:52:54,321
[No. 2 Liu Dai Yu's demonstration]

2627
01:52:54,321 --> 01:52:56,446
Don't be scared. It's already dead.

2628
01:52:56,446 --> 01:52:58,760
Why is she doing that?
Why hold your hand like that?

2629
01:52:58,760 --> 01:52:59,934
What is this?

2630
01:52:59,934 --> 01:53:02,622
- I didn't want to get too close.
- I see.

2631
01:53:02,622 --> 01:53:05,838
[Keeping distance!]

2632
01:53:05,838 --> 01:53:08,415
[A different side of the Chinese food
warrior in front of a frog]

2633
01:53:09,310 --> 01:53:11,358
I have to do it.

2634
01:53:12,990 --> 01:53:17,614
[Taking a deep breath to focus]

2635
01:53:18,770 --> 01:53:20,094
Okay.

2636
01:53:20,094 --> 01:53:22,878
It's okay, it's okay.

2637
01:53:23,678 --> 01:53:26,030
[Sunny strikes with force,
cutting them to the right size]

2638
01:53:26,030 --> 01:53:28,302
[Everyone nods in approval]
You're doing well.

2639
01:53:29,041 --> 01:53:30,462
[Picking up speed]
Grab it, grab it.

2640
01:53:30,462 --> 01:53:32,622
- I'm getting the hang of it.
- That's it.

2641
01:53:32,622 --> 01:53:35,809
I just hated the feeling of touching them.

2642
01:53:36,506 --> 01:53:38,878
I forgot about being the undercover rookie.

2643
01:53:38,878 --> 01:53:40,830
I thought I should hurry, so I let it go.

2644
01:53:40,830 --> 01:53:42,446
I did realize it a moment later,

2645
01:53:42,446 --> 01:53:45,726
but I just thought,
"Whatever," and chopped away.

2646
01:53:45,726 --> 01:53:48,815
[Rhythmic knife work]
[Clean and precise]

2647
01:53:48,815 --> 01:53:50,286
He was watching closely from behind.

2648
01:53:50,286 --> 01:53:51,854
Our MZ rookie was staring at me.

2649
01:53:51,854 --> 01:53:53,662
MZ. Our MZ rookie.

2650
01:53:53,662 --> 01:53:57,102
[The subtle aura of a master]

2651
01:53:57,102 --> 01:54:01,088
Sunny seems to know her way around a knife.

2652
01:54:02,212 --> 01:54:04,529
She's not a complete novice.

2653
01:54:04,529 --> 01:54:07,569
She seemed to have some basic skills.

2654
01:54:07,569 --> 01:54:11,678
[The Head of Prep is impressed]
Even when I taught her something,

2655
01:54:11,678 --> 01:54:13,598
she picked it up very quickly.

2656
01:54:13,598 --> 01:54:15,758
The results were different

2657
01:54:15,758 --> 01:54:20,302
from when I first started.

2658
01:54:20,302 --> 01:54:24,990
There was a big gap.

2659
01:54:28,030 --> 01:54:30,158
[Identity at risk]

2660
01:54:30,158 --> 01:54:32,878
[Will her life as a rookie go smoothly?]

2661
01:54:34,680 --> 01:54:37,086
I think she knows what she's doing.

2662
01:54:37,086 --> 01:54:40,014
[Identity at risk on the first day?]

2663
01:54:41,390 --> 01:54:43,230
[The suspicious rookies'...]

2664
01:54:43,902 --> 01:54:47,054
[unconcealable skills?]

2665
01:54:47,054 --> 01:54:49,152
Sunny must have learned this before.

2666
01:54:49,152 --> 01:54:52,206
[To pull off the perfect undercover job]
How can we fit into this system?

2667
01:54:52,206 --> 01:54:53,778
[The survival strategy they chose]

2668
01:54:54,494 --> 01:54:57,310
[Acting overly friendly?]
Tagliatelle are six.

2669
01:54:57,310 --> 01:54:58,702
[Flustered]

2670
01:54:58,702 --> 01:55:00,670
- Exactly.
- Yes.

2671
01:55:00,670 --> 01:55:02,318
[The Undercover Trio's]

2672
01:55:02,318 --> 01:55:04,926
[Day 1 of surviving as rookies]
Hello.

2673
01:55:04,926 --> 01:55:06,250
Like this.

2674
01:55:06,250 --> 01:55:08,309
[Working hard on social skills]
I can't work.

2675
01:55:09,082 --> 01:55:12,110
[Will the undercover rookies' strategy work?]

2676
01:55:12,110 --> 01:55:14,574
[But the real work starts now]

2677
01:55:17,614 --> 01:55:18,974
[Mainland undercover job: Day 1]

2678
01:55:18,974 --> 01:55:22,302
[First service begins!]

2679
01:55:22,302 --> 01:55:25,402
I can't handle this. I can't handle it.

2680
01:55:25,402 --> 01:55:26,798
[Wary]
It was a bit overwhelming.

2681
01:55:26,798 --> 01:55:27,816
It was chaotic.

2682
01:55:27,816 --> 01:55:31,470
[The reality of the kitchen freezes the pros]
Move faster!

2683
01:55:31,470 --> 01:55:33,230
[The local chefs are incredibly strict]
You should always start from the ends.

2684
01:55:33,230 --> 01:55:35,742
[Wait!]
Put it on the small plate.

2685
01:55:35,742 --> 01:55:39,114
[The senior's close supervision is tough...]

2686
01:55:40,157 --> 01:55:41,408
No.

2687
01:55:41,408 --> 01:55:42,706
This is a problem.

2688
01:55:42,706 --> 01:55:45,698
[An accident finally occurs]

2689
01:55:46,574 --> 01:55:48,440
<i>It's all okay.</i>

2690
01:55:48,440 --> 01:55:49,649
[I'm not okay...]

2691
01:55:49,649 --> 01:55:52,667
[What fate awaits the undercover rookies?]

2692
01:55:52,667 --> 01:55:54,522
No!
